President Donald Trump and First Lady Melania Trump are hosting the Trump Administration's second Congressional Picnic on the South Lawn. The event will be a bipartisan evening of music and fun, with a Summer Solstice theme to celebrate the start of the summer season. Lawn games, festival vendors, face painting, and ferris wheel rides will be part of the festivities. The menu will feature traditional picnic fare prepared by the White House Executive Chef, including charred lemon chicken, grilled plank salmon, charcoal grilled rib eye steak, and Baja shrimp tacos. The event will also include performances by "The President's Own" United States Marine Band and The United States Navy Band Cruisers. President Trump will make brief remarks. The First Lady expressed her excitement for the event, stating that it's an opportunity for elected officials to come together as a community.